.TH KBIT\-TORRENT 1 "2026-02-25" "kbit-torrent" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kbit\-torrent \- minimal BitTorrent CLI client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kbit\-torrent
.I command
.RI [ argument ]
.RI [ verbose ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kbit\-torrent
is a minimal BitTorrent client written in Go.
It provides CLI commands for working with
.I .torrent
files, including parsing metadata and discovering peers via trackers.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BI parse " <file>"
Parse a
.I .torrent
file and print its metadata summary, including name, info hash, length,
tracker URL, and discovered peers.
.TP
.BI handshake " <file>"
Perform a BitTorrent handshake with a peer.
Prompts interactively for a peer address in
.I host:port
format.
.TP
.BI download " <file>"
Download the torrent described by
.IR <file> .
Validates available peers, collects piece availability (bitfields),
sorts pieces by rarity (rarest-first), and writes the downloaded data
to disk. Progress is reported to stderr.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B verbose
Pass
.B verbose
as the fifth argument to enable verbose logging output.
.SH EXAMPLES
Parse a torrent file:
.PP
.RS
.EX
kbit\-torrent parse example.torrent
.EE
.RE
.PP
Perform a handshake with a peer (prompts for host:port):
.PP
.RS
.EX
kbit\-torrent handshake example.torrent
.EE
.RE
.PP
Download a torrent:
.PP
.RS
.EX
kbit\-torrent download example.torrent
.EE
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I bin/kbit\-torrent
Compiled binary produced by
.BR make (1).
